caption: Best coffee with oatmilk I tried so far
Excellent food, friendly staff and great location!
Who knew that a shrimp salad on bread exists? Want some food that you aren’t sure what it is but you want to try something new that isn’t super expensive? This is it!

Had two Delicious semlor here for Semla day 2021 - one Finnish and one Swedish. Brought back our time living in Sweden and the most delicious national holiday I know of. Authentic taste at a delightful cafe. Will definitely be back!
Delicious food and sweets from Nordic countries.

Absolutely adorable. I went during Jan 2021 (Covid times) and sat outside near a little space heater. The restaurant has excellent brunch food and a good beer selection. I had the bratwurst and the Swedish pancakes. Everything was very good and fresh. You order inside and the staff will deliver it to your table.
Coffee was burned and the quiche was stale and not fully baked. It was a disappointing experience. Will be sticking to Java House.
Scandi cuisine from the former Finnish Embassy chef. So good, really friendly staff
Great outdoor seating, fantastic staff and tasty food.
Have eaten here outdoors and for takeaway several times. Food is consistently outstanding and filling! Friendly and helpful staff!
Delicious!!!
Always good

Wanted to try this place as the reviews were stellar, but was severely disappointed. Should’ve seen the warning sign when all their sandwiches were premade inside. The French toast, bratwurst (one small sausage cut in half longwise to take up more plate space), and eggs were served on disposable plates. Reminiscent of an elementary school lunch. Instantly regretted it walking home and seeing  people enjoying much better meals along 17th street. The cute aesthetic must be their saving grace.

The food is overpriced but passble. The majority of staff were rude and location is mosquito riddled. Really not one to repeat. Try once and dont repeat. There was one excellent waiter from Turkey. The rest were so rude.

Maybe this was a good spot pre pandemic but wow was this a huge disappointment. Food was exceedingly mediocre. I got a bratwurst and two eggs — all bland and tasted like high school cafeteria eggs with the tiniest brat. My friend got a dry and hardly sweet fresh toast with what tasted like cool whip canned cream (not sure this is the fabulous Scandinavian food others have had). On top of that it was all served on paper plates with plastic utensils... hardly what you want to eat your disappointing $30+ meal on. Sorry, won’t be coming back and others should stay away
The hot dog was delicious! And the alexander bar was so yummy!
Warm casual atmosphere (including comfortable patio space) with delicious food and friendly staff.
Love this spot! Service is great and the people there are so kind.

A healthy, delicious and friendly place. Unfortunately closed now for renovations. Just went there yesterday and seemed like it was under construction. Unfortunately not updated on Google... call ahead.

Earlier this year, my partner and I asked Mikko to cater our wedding. We had a wonderful tasting and loved working with Jessica on the event planning side of things.  Of course, when COVID knocked aside our plans, we had to change things entirely. Mikko and co were patient and accommodating and, when we finally did tie the knot, delivered the most amazing food for us and our guests! We can't recommend them highly enough!  A big thanks to Mikko, Eric, Jessica, and crew!
Fantastic Nordic food. Quaint neighborhood spot. Everything is excellent. Meatballs, any and all, are a must try.
I live to come to Mikko for an iced coffee (strong and delicious) and a pastry. They have plenty of outdoor seating in the shade and the employees are always very friendly and helpful.
Stopped by to stock up on Finnish goodies and a delicious lunch
A perfect place to pick up a midsommar feast!
Cheerful, friendly place with great food and warm and welcoming staff and owner. Got take out here today and can’t wait to go back!
Great food, even better people. Go see Mikko for a taste of Finland and other Nordic treats!
(Translated by Google) Great bargain  (Original) Great semla

Enjoyed my Swedish semla on Shrove Tuesday (fettisdag). Chef Mikko bakes Swedish & Finnish semlor. The restaurant/bakery/store offers a wide variety of Scandinavian delights & daily specials. Chef Mikko offers various events throughout the year.
Absolutely love everything about this place! Amazing selection of food, friendliest staff, and cute seating areas! I’d come here every day if I could.

This is our neighborhood go-to! We love everything about Mikko - the food, the drinks, the atmosphere, and the people. Sometimes we go multiple times per week, either for a delicious pastry in the morning, or a sit down dinner in the evening.  No matter what meal of the day, they have something scrumptious and for every price point.  The salmon with mushroom risotto is one of the best meals I've ever had, and the "Fish Soup Take 2" is one of my favorite cocktails. The owners and staff are all so friendly, the decor is cozy and warm in the winter, and dining al fresco is a delight in the summer. If I could give this lovely gem 6 stars, I would!
Excellent food, super friendly and attentive staff. Also has extensive assortment of Finnish sweets.
Eclectic neighborhood spot for coffee and smoked fish, Nordic style!
So good. Casual and cosy. Great drinks. The hotdog with shrimp remoulade is amazing. A nice atmosphere and chef and server were so kind. Pricey though.

I went here on a lovely date and got the smoked salmon grilled cheese. It was absolutely delicious and the side salad was yummy too, I particularly liked the strawberries. The atmosphere is authentically European and made me miss being abroad. My only critique is the coffee was lackluster and paled in comparison to their gorgeous array of pastries.
Cody, friendly, fun and full of Nordic things
Absolutely delicious!
Great coffee!
Delicious - chicken schnitzel.  Relaxed casual vibe. Beer, wine, and vodka too.  We will definitely return for more.
Food is fine, service was a bit of a mess. It's counter service, but a tab system but... I don't quite know. Good for a snack, not sure otherwise.
Sandwiches on rye bread are THE BEST!
Delightful. Fish soup broth, light but full of briney flavor and fish pieces flavorful. Love their hearty breads.
Great food with Nordic flawors
Holly herring greatness! And the dog Luna was fabulous. Great job Tracy for rescuing her, and letting us pet her 🙏🏼
Very tasty dishes!!
Very good and quite authentic!
The wait time wasn't so bad, and I came on a busy than usual day. Fortunately, the service was quick and courteous. The food was a lot but I'm glad for that.
Great salmon sandwiches. Finnish chocolates & salmiakki ice cream for desert.

very great for my first time trying! very clean and staff friendly and helpful. has a nice café atmosphere and there is also an area to sit outside. food (i had gravlax on rye) was very tasty and something that i'd definately recommend!  food portions were a little small and it was a little expensive fot how much food i got, but it was certainly worth it.  if you're looking to try something new or some tasty pastries, i'd recommend Mikko in a heartbeat!

This place is the best! The people who run it are so friendly, there is a great neighborhood feel to the restaurant/cafe, and the food is delicious. The brunch is especially fantastic with unique and scrumptious french toast (using cardamom bread) and delicious and substantially-sized smoked salmon eggs benedict. They have nice indoor and outdoor seating options. I like that they have pastries and ready-made food, as well as high-quality prepared-to-order meals. Other highlights have been a Nordic mulled wine in the winter and delicious soups and grilled cheese.
This is a wonderful place. We just had savory snacks, but it was all wonderful. Don't leave without getting some Finnish treats.
Very nice little restaurant filled with Finnish delicacies and great food and drinks

We brought my parents here for my Mom's birthday. It was really great -- all the food was delicious, freshly prepared, and the staff was very friendly and attentive. Awesome authentic Nordic food and excellent service.
Great food and prompt service. First come, first serve, outside seating. We didn't have to wait at all.
Great food, great coffee and great pastries. Was a wonderful birthday lunch!
The only thing better than the delicious food and  charming little café was the service, Eric was a delight to talk to as he explained the origins of nearly every item on the menu!
Good Finnish food.

Really wanted to like this place but the food isn't up to par with the price. Rice in Karelian pastry was dry and old, egg butter tasteless. Hardly warm on the outside and cold inside. But it is the only place in DC to get Finnish food as far as I know.
Washington prices but you are limited on your options for Finnish gravlax and rye bread combo
Best Nordic Food in Town. Good place for delicious foods.
Nordic food is hip!
had the gravlax sandwich via Amazon order. Did not taste nor saw any mustard nor dill. Salmon was very good.
Good food, excessively pricey

Amazing service and wonderful food! The staff and owner were so kind and warm this has easily become my favorite place in DC.  It is hard for me to say if I liked the food or the people there the most because they were both such high quality.  I can't wait to return.
This small cafe is super charming! Highly recommend the fish soup with grilled cheese!

Very light, delicious food. Perfect if you want to eat healthy but want to enjoy a tasty treat. 100% chef material. Love the staff. Especially when they sing, I love the energy. Shout out to the singing staff, you make this world a better place!!
Mikko is a wonderful small and cozy spot. Scandinavian food is a truly underrated cuisine and their pastries and coffee are fit for any occasion.
The staff was incredibly friendly and attentive. Pastries are amazing. And the coffee was among the best iPad (I drink it black so I pay attention to quality). Awesome!
I strongly recommend visiting this place. The food and drinks are delicious, the people are friendly!

Mikko is a tiny, cute Nordic restaurant that also sells sandwiches and pastries. The place is festively painted bright red and blue. Most of the menu consists of fish dishes, but there's something for everyone.
Very interesting place. Nice European sandwiches and good coffee.
Amazing food with a super nice staff and some inventive drinks. They make you feel like a regular the first time you walk in. Pro tip: Get the mushroom soup; you're welcome.
Excellent food and atmosphere!

The food is delicious and authentic. The staff are so friendly. This is an amazing neighborhood place where you will want to come back over and over to try the rotating menu. I've had wonderful dinners, wonderful desserts, and even a great time just having a snack and coffee.
Quality of food is high, with a price to match. I still love the place!
Great food and they serve I'll coffee, my favorite.
Delicious food by a world famous chef!

Pricey but good and unique. Customer service was attentive and kind. The portions are just small for the price.  I am a fan of small portions, but the price is steep for them, especially for a casual cafe.
Lovely new spot! Well made Nordic food, patio seating and a great place.

What an amazing little hidden space! I would have totally missed it if I hadn’t been walking right past it. Really fair prices, delicious food (try the salmon quiche!), and great coffee. The staff are all delightful, and the music (currently, a Finnish radio station) is lovely.  Adding this to my DC favorites!
Finally, Nordic options in DC

Even though Swedish blood runs think through my veins, I am not one for Nordic cooking, mainly because the amount of seafood they use. Mikko changed my opinion after just one visit.  My Swedish friend and I grabbed lunch on a Friday at Mikko. It was a perfect sunny day and Mikko's was the ideal spot with it's patio seating and open window concept. It also is the best dressed restaurant in DC with blues and reds on brand, evoking a brighter summer.  The staff are friendly from the host to chef Mikko himself. You order inside from their limited, yet excellent lunch menu. They have pastries (sweet and savory) and packages snacks from northern Europe. I ordered the Swedish hot dog with shrimp skagen (like a dill and shrimp potato salad) and it was legit and tasty!  As my friend and I were dining outside, the server brought us free cinnamon roll treats and an extra serving of shrimp skagen. Wow!  If you want a friendly and tasty restaurant, walk to Dupont Circle to Mikko!
Delicious, healthy food, and fun people to talk to!

Great spot for delicious food that isn't common in DC. Quality herring, small plates are tasty but very small (and not cheap), soup and grilled cheese though is a tasty, affordable, and filling meal.  Nice "Nordic" style ambiance. The seating inside is mostly bar style with two small tables. The remaining tables are outside in a lovely patio.
Love it! Totally recommend.

Great spot for Nordic cuisine. My Finnish wife said "we teleported to Finland for a meal." We enjoyed fish soup and swedish hotdog. The meal was finished with lettu crepes, which are to die for. The house cocktails was a phenomenal pairing.

Space is adorable but the breakfast item prices felt high for what you got. And the breakfast items were stored in a way that made ones with fish and vegetables look unsightly. This however did not impact the taste; which was great. The staff were extremely pleasant, might revisit again for lunch / dinner and give it another go.
Stopped by for morning coffee -- great bright space and decor, super friendly staff and lovely coffee.  I look forward to coming back to explore the rest of the menu!

Amazingly friendly staff.  Baked goods are super tasty.  Many of the dishes are takes or variations on traditional Scandinavian dishes.  The hot dog is not a tunnebrodsrulle (even though it has shrimp salad) and the meatballs are not traditional Swedish meatballs.  As long as you're prepared for the twists, this place will blow your underkläder off.
Great food and great people!
Mikko Nordic fine food literally 👉DEFINES👈 the essence of every letter of fine dining!👌

Very good food and drink with a quaint little location. Dog friendly on the patio, which constitutes most of the seating.  They have loads of Finnish goods and personality to really spice things up. The pastries were fresh and flaky! If you like coffee and a meal this is a sweet spot.

It is really a charming place. Their menu is very creative and delicious. The prices are very reasonable and the staff is super nice. The place has a creative decor with attention to detail. There is also an outdoor space. I am a coffee person and love their coffee as well as cute white coffee cups. It is great place for a quick date or to hang out with friends or do some work on your laptop.   I would highly recommend it.

Enjoyed the delicious Shrimp Salad Skagen sandwich and my partner Matt loved the smoked salmon sandwich he ate.  Also picked up a loaf of the 7-grain seeded bread - yummy!!  Will definitely be eating here again!!
Fantastic food and wonderful service!! Definitely a great place to eat Nordic food.
Love this place! Delicious, very fresh food!
My favorite resto in DC right now.
Really great coffee, food, and service 👌
Unbelievable roast beef sandwich served open face with potato salad and crispy onion straws Also tried some blueberry cake Everything was fabulous!
Gravlax was OK. Get the Karelian.

Had just about all the small plates and everything was delicious. Staff was very friendly and attentive. I especially recommend the fish salad and the meatballs and will definitely come back again when I'm back in town. Thanks!
The coffee is good here 👍🏻
Delicious, fresh and inventive dishes. Can’t wait for the expanded menu!
My wife’s English teacher recommends this place and so do I!
Great, authentic Nordic dishes. Charming DuPont location.

Amazing food, very fresh! Great atmosphere! This definitely won’t be my last time. It was my first time I had the Shrimp Salad Skagen. The sandwich was so amazing and light. I wish I could have had another.
